        </div>
        <p>For more detailed information please refer to the documentation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-leaf">
        <h2><a name="media">Working with Media</a></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="content-leaf">
        <h2><a name="users">Managing Users</a></h2>
        <p>To manage users you need to login to the site with an user who has an administrator or user administrator
          role.
        </p>
        <br>
        <p>To manage users on the site goto /admin/people page</p>
        <p>To manage permissions on the site goto /people/permissions</p>
        <p>To manage roles on the site goto admin/people/roles</p>
        <br>
        <p>In addition to the administrator, anonymous and authenticated roles, your site comes pre-setup with the
          following roles -
        </p>
        <table class="diff-responsive-table">
          <thead>
          <th>Role</th>
          <th></th>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Content Administrator</td>
            <td>Has full control over the content on the site. Can create/edit/delete, publish/unpublish any
              content </td>
          <tr>
            <td>Content Author</td>
            <td>Can create/edit/delete own content.</td>
          <tr>
            <td>Content Editor</td>
            <td>Can create/edit any content, but cannot delete</td>
          <tr>
            <td>Developer</td>
            <td>Can create/edit new Site Studio components or edit existing ones</td>
          <tr>
            <td>Site Builder</td>
            <td>Can help building landing pages using Site Studio components</td>
          <tr>
            <td>Administrator</td>
            <td>Has full control over the site.</td>
          <tr>
            <td>User Administrator</td>
            <td>Can administer users on the site. This role can Add/Delete users as well as block/unblock users.</td>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div class="content-leaf">
        <h2><a name="menus">Building Menus</a></h2>
        <p>In ACMS, menu management is unchanged and follows the core Drupal workflow.
          Menus can be managed at /admin/structure/menu.
        </p>
        <p>ACMS comes pre-configured with header and footer menus.
          The menu that you see in the header of the site after installation is named as Main Navigation.
          You can access the menu admin/structure/menu/manage/main.
          Once you are on the page you can add/edit/delete and manage the links shown in the header
        </p>
        <img style="width:100%;" src="/{{ module_path[0] }}/assets/images/header.png"/>
        <p>Similar to the header menu, the footer menu also comes pre-configured with ACMS.
          The footer menu is displayed on the site in the footer region.
          You can access the menu admin/structure/menu/manage/footer.
          Once you are on the page you can add/edit/delete and manage the links shown in the footer
        </p>
        <img style="width:100%;" src="/{{ module_path[0] }}/assets/images/footer.png"/>
      </div>
      <div class="content-leaf">
        <h2><a name="forms">Creating Forms</a></h2>
        <p>Acquia CMS includes the Webform module to enable site builders to create forms through the administrative UI.
          We include one sample form in our public sector demo (‘Contact Us’ in the main menu)
          as an implementation example.
        </p>
        <p>There is extensive documentation on working with webforms on Drupal.org. Some key reference materials are:</p>
        <p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://www.drupal.org/node/2834423">Webform introduction</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.drupal.org/node/2837024">Features overview</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.drupal.org/node/2834424">Video tutorials</a></li>
        </ul>
        </p>
        <p>Additionally, Acquia Academy provides training materials on the Webform module here (include link).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-leaf">
        <h2><a name="site-studio">Working with Site Studio</a></h2>
        <p>ACMS is opinionated and integrated with other Acquia products out of the box.
          With the current version it comes pre-configured with Acquia Site Studio and has pre-built components.
        </p>
        <p>When you install ACMS and set up your Acquia Site Studio keys, you get the following components
          out of the box which will help you to get started with your site building right after installation.
        </p>
        <p>To use these components all you need to do is start creating page type of content.
          To do so head over to node/add/page
        </p>
        <img style="width:100%;" src="/{{ module_path[0] }}/assets/images/component-list-1.png"/>
        <img style="width:100%;" src="/{{ module_path[0] }}/assets/images/component-list-2.png"/>
        <img style="width:100%;" src="/{{ module_path[0] }}/assets/images/component-list-3.png"/>
      </div>
      <div class="content-leaf">
        <h2><a name="troubleshooting">Troubleshooting</a></h2>
        <p>Q. What should I do if maps are not being displayed on my places pages?</p>
        <p>For maps to be displayed correctly, you have to make sure you have set the correct Google API keys.
          You need to set the api keys at two places -
        </p>
        <p>
        <ol>
          <li>admin/config/system/geocoder/geocoder-provider/manage/googlemaps</li>
          <li>admin/cohesion/configuration/google-map-api-key</li>
        </ol>
        </p>
        <br>
        <P>Q. I would like to see a demo of the ACMS system?</P>
        <P>ACMS ships with a demo site which is not enabled by default.
          To enable the demo site, please head over to admin/modules page and install Acquia CMS PubSec Demo module
        </P>
        <br>
        <P>Q. I would like to see some default content after i install ACMS</P>
        <P>ACMS has a starter module available which has default content. To enable the starter module,
          please head over to the admin/modules page and install Acquia CMS Starter module.
        </P>
      </div>
